---
source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: "help(&[\"subvolume\", \"set-default\"])"
---
Set the default subvolume of a filesystem.

Accepts either a subvolume path (btrfs subvolume set-default /mnt/fs/subvol) or a numeric ID with a
filesystem path (btrfs subvolume set-default 256 /mnt/fs).

Usage: set-default <SUBVOL_OR_ID> [PATH]

Arguments:
  <SUBVOL_OR_ID>
          Subvolume path OR numeric subvolume ID

  [PATH]
          Filesystem mount point (required when first arg is a numeric ID)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
